hat the team lost 15 more games than it won, so the number of games lost is \\(W + 15\\). The total number of games played is the sum of games won and lost, so \\(T = W + (W + 15)\\). Substituting \\(W = \\frac{2}{9}T\\) into the equation, we get \\(T = \\frac{2}{9}T + \\frac{2}{9}T + 15\\). Simplifying, we find \\(T = 45\\). </think> <answer> 45 </answer>", "truth": "27", "reward_format": 1.0, "reward_answer": 0.0, "reward_total": 0.0}]